From f45effc751d8aca86b5da157122ee8bf26df77f1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lans Zhang <jia.zhang@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2009 13:38:42 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Race condition in pmem general log initialization causes instability

There is a window where pmem is enabled but the general
log handle hasn't yet been registered. If we try to do
a printk() during this window, the system will hang.

Signed-off-by: Lans Zhang <jia.zhang@windriver.com>
---
 mm/pmem/io.c |    8 +++++++-
 1 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/pmem/io.c b/mm/pmem/io.c
index 656b0d1..30f0e84 100644
--- a/mm/pmem/io.c
+++ b/mm/pmem/io.c
@@ -75,8 +75,14 @@ int pmem_read_data(pmem_handle_t handle, char *buffer, int size)
 	spinlock_t *lock = NULL;
 	unsigned long flags = 0;
 
+	/* There is a window where pmem is enabled but the handles have not yet
+	 * been registered.
+	 */
+	if (!handle)
+		goto done;
+
 #ifdef CONFIG_PMEM_DEBUG
-	if (!handle || !buffer || (size < 0)) {
+	if (!buffer || (size < 0)) {
 		PMEM_DPRINT("read: invalid arguments\n");
 		goto done;
 	}
